[In 1997 the deaths were first attributed to one of the Coxsackie group of
viruses, then to enterovirus type 71 (EV71), & a new virus was also
isolated. Consequently, the reports on ProMED-mail came out with a
confusing variety of titles. The Malaysian authorities are understandably
trying to defuse any panic and are stressing prevention. Whether or not
these deaths are in fact due to HFMD, which is caused by a variety of
enteroviruses, or to something else, the fact is that deaths with symptoms
of viral myocarditis have occurred in association with this HFMD epidemic.
It is hoped that adequate autopsy specimens have been available for
investigation Â– Mod.JW
